VALUES ('ba30abdc-3b3e-4ca7-8dcb-6f4b52c8e360', 'Which choice most accurately describes how the text develops its central claim?', 'Economists analyzing market 100004 observed that small retailers adapted faster than national chains when supply chains stalled, partly because they could reorder from local wholesalers within days. While big-box stores waited for centralized distribution centers to reopen, corner shops phoned alternate suppliers named in handwritten contact lists. The economists interviewed owners who shifted product mix toward shelf-stable goods and services that did not depend on overseas shipping. Still, a counter-perspective emerged when researchers documented outcomes the dominant model could not fully explain. National chains, bound to national contracts and uniform pricing algorithms, could not pivot as quickly without corporate approval cycles. The study does not', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It describes only the final paragraph''s policy recommendation without accounting for the theoretical setup and evidentiary middle the passage develops before reaching that recommendation in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"B","text":"It attributes personal ambition to the author instead of analyzing how the text moves from observation to qualified generalization across successive sentences as written here throughout, rather than importing","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."},{"id":"C","text":"It asserts that the author abandons the central inquiry midway, when the passage instead deepens that inquiry through concession and counterevidence in later sentences here throughout.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"D","text":"It outlines a widely held assumption, introduces research challenging its universal application, and clarifies how practitioners should interpret the moderated conclusion throughout overall in sum in context.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Correct (D). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
Focus on {{yellow:alternate}} in the passage. The structure item asks you to identify the passage organization before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Match structure to purpose
