VALUES ('329a3306-ea75-4010-bf73-4fdcfff93601', 'Which choice best characterizes the text''s rhetorical structure?', 'Archaeologists at site 100005 discovered that pottery shards contained residue of fermented grain, suggesting the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than daily meals. Layer analysis placed the shards in a ceremonial plaza rather than domestic kitchens, and nearby hearths showed feasting debris concentrated on solstice dates. Chemical tests identified compounds consistent with controlled fermentation but not with large-scale storage for everyday consumption. The team compared the findings with neighboring settlements where grain storage pits dominated the record. Nevertheless, subsequent fieldwork revealed limitations that the opening account had treated as settled fact. That contrast supports the interpretation that brewing here marked special occasions and', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It establishes a cause-and-effect claim, supplies seasonal field evidence, and acknowledges limitations before drawing implications as written here throughout overall in sum in context as written in sum in context as written.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (A). Correct (A). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"B","text":"It lists technical vocabulary from the opening sentences without showing how those terms support a cumulative argument across the full paragraph from mechanism to outcome here in context as written here throughout.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"C","text":"It predicts that the author will publish a memoir, a motivation the passage never discusses or reasonably implies from its expository structure and academic tone throughout, in a way that matches how.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."},{"id":"D","text":"It claims effects are analyzed before causes are defined, inverting the passage''s movement from causal mechanism to documented outcome in the study described overall in sum here throughout overall in sum in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
Focus on {{yellow:concentrated}} in the passage. The structure item asks you to identify the passage organization before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Match structure to purpose
