VALUES ('94c560f5-25fc-4f04-9dca-b4640410c1bc', 'Which choice most accurately describes how the text develops its central claim?', 'Psychologists testing memory task 100014 reported that participants who slept eight hours recalled word lists more accurately than those who stayed awake, even when both groups studied equally long. The awake group was kept in a quiet lounge with books and puzzles to prevent napping, yet their recall still lagged behind the sleep group on both immediate and delayed tests. Brain-imaging subsamples showed differences in hippocampal activity during retrieval, aligning with theories that sleep consolidates declarative memories. By contrast, later analysts argued that the initial synthesis overlooked boundary conditions essential to interpretation. The researchers caution that the study measured short lists under lab conditions and', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It asserts that the author abandons the central inquiry midway, when the passage instead deepens that inquiry through concession and counterevidence in later sentences overall in sum.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] [Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"B","text":"It outlines a widely held assumption, introduces research challenging its universal application, and clarifies how practitioners should interpret the moderated conclusion in sum in context as written.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (B). Correct (B). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"C","text":"It describes only the final paragraph''s policy recommendation without accounting for the theoretical setup and evidentiary middle the passage develops before reaching that recommendation in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] [Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"D","text":"It attributes personal ambition to the author instead of analyzing how the text moves from observation to qualified generalization across successive sentences as written here throughout.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] [Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
Focus on {{yellow:delayed}} in the passage. The structure item asks you to identify the passage organization before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Match structure to purpose
